  <bioghist id="aspace_d428e56c3f4143198ab378c9fc6ef9f0">
    <head>ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY</head>
<p>The Cascadilla School was a boarding school for boys in Ithaca, New York.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_88170f80725333c451200cb3c26d9a72">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Catalogues (1887, 1893-1894, 1896-1897, 1923-1924, 1924-1925, 1931-1932), prospectus and yearbook (ca. 1900), and pictures of the school (ca. 1900).</p><p> Accession folder contains a "Catalogue of Students of the Cascadilla School, 1876-94."</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_22ec907dc89ccb52185f6037c750683a">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Cascadilla School publications, #1152. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
